✅ FULL SETUP INSTRUCTIONS (FOR WINDOWS/MAC/LINUX)
🛠 Prerequisites:
Install Git: https://git-scm.com/downloads

Create a GitHub account: https://github.com

Optional: Use VS Code for easier management

🔁 1. Open Terminal or Git Bash
Navigate into your project folder:

bash
Copy code
cd path/to/your/fundraising-portal
📦 2. Initialize Git
bash
Copy code
git init
📝 3. Create a .gitignore file (optional but recommended)
Create a file named .gitignore in the root of your project and add:

bash
Copy code
node_modules/
.env
.DS_Store
This keeps unnecessary files out of Git.

📸 4. Stage and Commit All Files
bash
Copy code
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - fundraising portal"
🌐 5. Create a GitHub Repository
Go to https://github.com/new

Name it something like fundraising-portal

Keep it Public or Private

DO NOT initialize with README (we already have files locally)

Click Create Repository

🔗 6. Connect Local Repo to GitHub
You'll see instructions like this from GitHub — use them:

bash
Copy code
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/fundraising-portal.git
git push -u origin main
Replace YOUR-USERNAME with your GitHub username.

✅ DONE! Your Project is Now on GitHub 🎉
You can verify by visiting:

bash
Copy code
https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/fundraising-portal
🧠 Bonus (Optional):
